<qti-assessment-item xmlns="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqtiasi_v3p0" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" identifier="Q28_v8" title="Q28_v8" time-dependent="false" adaptive="false" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqtiasi_v3p0 https://purl.imsglobal.org/spec/qti/v3p0/schema/xsd/imsqti_asiv3p0_v1p0.xsd">
  <qti-response-declaration identifier="RESPONSE" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier">
    <qti-correct-response>
      <qti-value>ChoiceB</qti-value>
    </qti-correct-response>
  </qti-response-declaration>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="FEEDBACK" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier"/>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="SOLUTION" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier"/>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="SCORE" cardinality="single" base-type="float">
    <qti-default-value>
      <qti-value>0</qti-value>
    </qti-default-value>
  </qti-outcome-declaration>
  <qti-item-body>
    <p>En un mapa, 3 cm representan 12 km de distancia real.</p>
    <p>Si en el mapa la distancia entre dos ciudades es de 10 cm, ¿cuál de las siguientes distancias reales es coherente con la escala del mapa?</p>
    <qti-choice-interaction response-identifier="RESPONSE" shuffle="false" max-choices="1">
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceA">4 km<qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceA" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. Si 3 cm representan 12 km, entonces 1 cm representa <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mrow><mn>12</mn><mo>÷</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow></math> km. Por lo tanto, 10 cm representan <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mrow><mn>10</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>40</mn></mrow></math> km, no 4 km.</qti-feedback-inline></qti-simple-choice>
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceB">40 km<qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceB" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">¡Correcto! Si 3 cm representan 12 km, entonces 1 cm representa <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mrow><mn>12</mn><mo>÷</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow></math> km. Así, 10 cm representan <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mrow><mn>10</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>40</mn></mrow></math> km. Por eso, 40 km es coherente con la escala del mapa.</qti-feedback-inline></qti-simple-choice>
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceC">120 km<qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceC" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. La escala indica que 3 cm representan 12 km, no 10 cm. Primero, 1 cm representa <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mrow><mn>12</mn><mo>÷</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow></math> km. Entonces, para 10 cm la distancia real es <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mrow><mn>10</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>40</mn></mrow></math> km. Por lo tanto, 120 km no es coherente con la escala.</qti-feedback-inline></qti-simple-choice>
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceD">3 km<qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceD" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. Si 3 cm representan 12 km, entonces 1 cm representa <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mrow><mn>12</mn><mo>÷</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow></math> km. Para 10 cm, la distancia real debe ser <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mrow><mn>10</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>40</mn></mrow></math> km. Por eso, 3 km no satisface la escala dada.</qti-feedback-inline></qti-simple-choice>
    </qti-choice-interaction>
    <qti-feedback-block identifier="show" outcome-identifier="SOLUTION" show-hide="show">
      <qti-content-body>
        <p><strong>Resolución paso a paso</strong></p>
        <ol>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 1: Identificar la escala del mapa</strong></p>
            <p>El enunciado dice que 3 cm en el mapa representan 12 km en la realidad.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 2: Hallar cuánto representa 1 cm</strong></p>
            <p>Dividimos la distancia real por la distancia en el mapa:</p>
            <p>
              <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML">
                <mrow>
                  <mn>12</mn><mo>÷</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn>
                </mrow>
              </math>
            </p>
            <p>Entonces, 1 cm representa 4 km.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 3: Calcular cuánto representan 10 cm</strong></p>
            <p>Como 1 cm representa 4 km, 10 cm representan:</p>
            <p>
              <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML">
                <mrow>
                  <mn>10</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>40</mn>
                </mrow>
              </math>
            </p>
            <p>Por lo tanto, la distancia real es 40 km.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 4: Comparar con las alternativas</strong></p>
            <p>La alternativa que coincide con 40 km es la opción B.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Conclusión</strong></p>
            <p>La distancia real coherente con la escala del mapa es 40 km.</p>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </qti-content-body>
    </qti-feedback-block>
  </qti-item-body>
  <qti-response-processing>
    <qti-response-condition>
      <qti-response-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceB</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SCORE">
          <qti-base-value base-type="float">1</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceB</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceC</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceC</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceD</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceD</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else>
    </qti-response-condition>
  </qti-response-processing>
</qti-assessment-item>